# C++ Coding Style and Naming

- Language level: C++17; use Qt idioms and types where appropriate.
- Formatting: 4-space indentation, 100-column limit. Enforced by [.clang-format](mdc:.clang-format) and [.editorconfig](mdc:.editorconfig).
- Class names: PascalCase (e.g., `QtLucideIconPainter`).
- Method names: lowerCamelCase (e.g., `initLucide`).
- Enum values: snake_case (e.g., `Icons::alert_circle`).
- Place implementation in [`src/`](mdc:src) and public headers in [`include/QtLucide/`](mdc:include/QtLucide).
- Document public APIs with Doxygen comments (see docs in [`docs/api`](mdc:docs/api)).

Do not edit generated headers: [`include/QtLucide/QtLucideEnums.h`](mdc:include/QtLucide/QtLucideEnums.h), [`include/QtLucide/QtLucideStrings.h`](mdc:include/QtLucide/QtLucideStrings.h). Regenerate via tools when needed.

